State MSM Profile: Montana

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Montana

An estimated 6,374 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Montana in 2013, representing 0.1% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 386,653 adult men of Montana, 1.6% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Montana resided in non-metropolitan, or rural, counties (55.6%). No MSM in Montana resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Montana, 2013

MSM in Montana Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Montana, Missoula County had the largest population of MSM at 1,240, representing 19.5% of all MSM in the state. Wibaux County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Montana at 10.0%. This was greater than the percentage for Montana as a whole, which was 1.6% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Montana Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Missoula Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Missoula MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Montana at 1,240, or 19.5% of all MSM in the state. Of the 44,053 adult men in Missoula, an estimated 2.8% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Billings Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Billings MSA had a population of 1,142 MSM, or 17.9% of all MSM in Montana. Of the 59,818 adult men in Billings, an estimated 1.9% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Great Falls Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Great Falls MSA had a population of 449 MSM, or 7.0% of all MSM in Montana. Of the 31,148 adult men in Great Falls, an estimated 1.4% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
